Substitute \(x = \frac{1}{3}\):

\[5f\left(\frac{1}{3}\right) - \frac{1}{3}f(3) = \frac{1}{17} \left(\frac{1}{3}\right)^2 = \frac{1}{153}\]

This gives the system:

5f(3) - 3f\left(\frac{1}{3}\right) = \frac{9}{17} \\
5f\left(\frac{1}{3}\right) - \frac{1}{3}f(3) = \frac{1}{153}
\end{cases}\]

Let \(a = f(3)\) and \(b = f\left(\frac{1}{3}\right)\):

\[\begin{cases}
5a - 3b = \frac{9}{17} \\
5b - \frac{1}{3}a = \frac{1}{153}
\end{cases}\]

Multiply the second equation by 3:

\[15b - a = \frac{1}{51}\]

The system is:

\[\begin{cases}
5a - 3b = \frac{9}{17} \\
-a + 15b = \frac{1}{51}
\end{cases}\]

Solve by elimination. Multiply the first equation by 1 and the second by 5:

\[\begin{cases}
5a - 3b = \frac{9}{17} \\
-5a + 75b = \frac{5}{51}

\[72b = \frac{9}{17} + \frac{5}{51} = \frac{27}{51} + \frac{5}{51} = \frac{32}{51}\]

\[-a + 15 \cdot \frac{4}{459} = \frac{1}{51}\]

\[-a = \frac{9}{459} - \frac{60}{459} = -\frac{51}{459}\]

\[a = \frac{51}{459} = \frac{1}{9}\]

Thus, \(f(3) = \frac{1}{9}\).
